English: to confuse, to distract, to perplex
to aspirate, to breathe, to respire
to try, to attempt, to practise, to rehearse
to confess, to justify, to proclaim
to beseech, to conjure, to implore
to climb, to clamber, to scramble
to assenble, to collect, to compile, to convene
to blemish, to infringe, to outrage
to divide, to disperse, to diverge, to isolate
to decline, to descend, to dismount
to repair, to correct, to rectify
to answer, to counter, to respond
to accredit, to bequeath, to commend, to consign
to tell, to relate, to narrate
to bandage, to envelop, to swaddle
